## Summary

Repairs the pre-existing CI failures that were intentionally kept out of the canvas-performance PR.

- passes `+SpherePacking` to `lean-action`, so the external dependency root is built before kernel extraction;
- uses the same explicit root in the Mathlib-bump workflow and its generated validation notes;
- replaces the stale `BlueprintGraph` test's dependency on removed template demo content with an isolated temporary fixture;
- applies the existing Prettier-only changes in `blueprint.config.json` and `scripts/lib/blueprint-model.mjs`.

The workspace intentionally has no default Lake target, so plain `lake build` succeeds without producing
`SpherePacking.olean`. Building `+SpherePacking` matches the command already documented in `lakefile.toml`.

## Validation

Passed with Node 22.17.0:

- `npm test`;
- `npm run check`;
- clean content build and `QUARTZ_CONTENT_ROOT=docs npm run build`;
- `npm run test:blueprint`;
- agent build plus 79 workflow checks;
- 752 agent runtime tests;
- agent docs and shell checks;
- `lake build +SpherePacking`;
- `npm run blueprint:sync` (1,331 declarations, 140 nodes, 287 edges);
- generated `blueprint-data.json` and `dep-graph.canvas` remained unchanged;
- `git diff --check`.

This PR is independent of the canvas-performance patch in #4.

